<h2>The Face in the Window</h2>
<p>
    Sofia began noticing the face during rainy nights when the windows reflected more of the room than the darkness outside. At first it looked like an illusion standing behind her reflection — a tall man with hollow eyes and skin as gray as wet paper. Every time she turned around, nobody was there. But each night, the figure appeared closer in the glass. Soon she could see details of his cracked lips and the dirt packed beneath his fingernails.
</p>
<br>
<p>
    One stormy evening, the power went out while Sofia was brushing her teeth. She used her phone flashlight to navigate the apartment and accidentally caught her reflection in the bathroom mirror. The man stood directly behind her in the reflection, smiling faintly. Frozen in fear, she spun around and found the bathroom completely empty. Then her phone buzzed with a camera notification showing a newly saved photo taken seconds earlier from inside the bathroom.
</p>
<br>
<p>
    The image revealed Sofia staring at the mirror while the gray-skinned man leaned over her shoulder. Terrified, she deleted the photo and smashed the mirror with a chair. For a moment everything became silent except for the rain outside. Then every broken shard began reflecting the man’s face separately, each version smiling wider than the last. Before the police arrived after neighbors heard her screaming, someone inside the apartment had pulled all the curtains shut from the inside.
</p>